  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to assess different doses of a new drug (BAY 59-7939), taken as
      a tablet, are safe and can help prevent blood clots forming after a hip replacement
      operation. Patients undergoing hip replacement surgery are at risk of developing blood clots.
      To reduce this risk treatment to prevent clots forming is routinely given. The current
      treatments can include injections under the skin or other treatments that need frequent blood
      tests to monitor levels of drug in the body. Therefore there is a need for new drugs, which
      are easier to give and need less monitoring.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
